fields.title: Brandfolder
fields.description:
### About the Brandfolder app:

The Brandfolder app is a widget that allows editors to select media from their Brandfolder account. Simply click `Select an asset on Brandfolder` and select the asset you want to be referenced from your entry.

The IDs and URLs of selected assets are then stored in Contentful. Inside your client application, you then fetch content from Contentful and resolve any additional details on assets by using the IDs to fetch more data from Brandfolder's API.

### Requirements
To use this app, you will need:

- Your Brandfolder API Key [https://brandfolder.com/profile#integrations](https://brandfolder.com/profile#integrations)
- A content type with a field of type JSON object to hold the references to Brandfolder assets

### Screenshots:

![Brandfolder screenshot](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/5t3uBh0eZKfggUfZlTnAUJ/0f2ba659f251f95d1ff4b7ca921fd8bc/editor-view.png)
fields.tagLine: Find and use brand, marketing and product assets from your Brandfolder library

fields.title: Jira
fields.description:
### About the Jira app

The Jira app in Contentful gives you a clear overview of the Jira tickets attached to content entries, reporters, or assignees. The overview of both open and resolved tickets gives teams context so they can collaborate effectively with editing/or implementing content changes. 

Also, by connecting Jira and Contentful, all users involved in content creation can continue working in the software they prefer without the need to switch between services. 

---

### Features:

- Editors can see which tickets match an entry 
- Link and preview the ticket in the sidebar
- Quickly navigate into a Jira issue

---

### Requirements:

To use this app you will need:

- A Jira account and project
- A Jira admin to install the [companion app](https://marketplace.atlassian.com/apps/1221865/contentful?hosting=cloud&tab=overview) in your Jira instance

---

### Screenshots:

![Jira UI](https://images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/3OlrOjIeYyJ083I4nvqIOi/84e4f5bfe50b1e0f46960796693fda00/Screen_Shot_2020-02-03_at_15.20.26.png)
fields.tagLine: Collaborate seamlessly on content edits with the Jira app

fields.title: Netlify
fields.description:
### About the app

The Netlify app makes creating and updating content on your site easier. The app removes the need to navigate between platforms, giving editors full control of everything from previewing to deploying changes. Content writers and editors can trigger Netlify builds with one click in the sidebar. 

See build status in real-time, track progress and view recent changes all from within the web app. 


---

### What you can do with the Netlify app: 

- Trigger Netlify builds with one click in the sidebar
- Display build status so editors don't preview outdated sites
- Bring Netlify functionality into the Contentful web app
- Configure on a per-content-type level 

### Requirements:

- A static site based on a static site generator such as Gatsby, Middleman or Hugo
- Your site configured to load content from Contentful and its code pushed to a remote repository, such as GitHub or Gitlab
- A Netlify setup where the site is connected to the remote repository and enabled for continuous deployment

---

### Screenshots

![Netlify config](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/4Rf8yoGPw4AQwdMboiVwhF/a0a9a8b8e73a5ace1fdf78adebc24a49/apps-netlify-site-setup.b4a24a69c0.png)

![Netlify sidebar](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/RrSqXTcdlpfkPt7sJzkEb/57172d0fd3eaa36a5ab90e7d183ed171/apps-netlify-sidebar.0ffd73e12b.png)
fields.tagLine: Easily build and preview sites with the Netlify app

fields.title: Optimizely
fields.description:
### About the Optimizely app

Optimizely is a leading feature flagging and experimentation platform. The Optimizely app offers a simple way to run experiments with content, helping you make smarter data-backed decisions. Marketers can optimize content, obtain better insights, and iterate continuously without leaving Contentful. 


---

### Features:

- Run A/B tests or multivariate tests on structured content (copy, components, layouts and pages)
- Marketers don’t have to be dependent on developers to lead experimentation 
- Reduce the amount of manual work needed to set up experiments


---

### Installation:

Installing this app will:

- Create a new content type called "Variation Container" 
- Create "Variation Container" entries
- Read your projects, experiments and variations from Optimizely

---

### Requirements:

- An Optimizely full stack plan with access to the REST API

---

### Screenshots:

![Optimizely editor](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/6BKTGsRNAzlQgllHDclqYe/ad9bad07083d102d1deff54a6a62e57f/optimizely-editor.png)
fields.tagLine: Enable experimentation at scale with the Optimizely app

fields.title: Smartling
fields.description:
### About the Smartling app 

The Smartling app allows editors to access their translation services from the Contentful web app allowing editors to streamline their workflows and launch international content faster. 

Collaboration on localized content becomes easier and faster as progress on translated content in Smartling can be tracked via the Contentful web app. Editors can link through from Contentful to Smartling to make requests, as well as see the status of the translation for the current Contentful entry. 

Content writers, campaign managers and field marketers have greater oversight of overall progress for each locale and language in the Contentful web-app and can push any changes directly to any device for the best digital experience.

---

### Features:

- Quick access to Smartling 
- See translation status by locale 
- Easily navigate to translation files in Smartling 

---

### Requirements:

- A Smartling project using Contentful connector
- Contentful admin support to install the app

---

### Screenshots
![Smartling UI](https://images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/197oHOVBA6TQkeaCLCWUH2/f05327c0a2f166fa94218415babb44ca/smartling-ui.png)
fields.tagLine: Automate and streamline localization with the Smartling app

fields.title: Gatsby Cloud
fields.description:
### About the app
The Gatsby app offers a fast and easy way to preview content changes on your website directly from Contentful. Editors can feel confident about their changes before they are live. 

---

### Features:

With the Gatsby app you can:

- Preview a build of a Gatsby site
- Trigger a manual build of a Gatsby site

---

### Screenshots

![Gatsby cloud](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/1zISSOxs4Cm0cIDPsbf1FV/7815345d53a95a0934c9bcc39829f9c5/gatsby-preview.png)
fields.tagLine: Instantly see content changes on your website with the Gatsby app

fields.title: Google Analytics
fields.description:
### About the Google Analytics app:

Each content entry linked on any page that gets traffic with a URL is tracked with the Google Analytics (GA) app in Contentful. Editors can simply look at the performance of each content piece instead of trawling through lengthy GA account reports. 

This is useful for teams that use different space environments. The app narrows down the reports and data to individual content pieces, content types, and entries. 

---

### Features:

- Embed specific content reports in the sidebar
- Link directly to Google Analytics report for the entry page

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need:

- Google project ID
- Content type(s) with a slug field

---

### Screenshots:

![ga-sidebar](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/7zgLkoPahgp4aahUdRlR1O/c019a1443bcb2dac8d1d7cc616cd5512/ga-sidebar.png)
fields.tagLine: Track content performance via the Google Analytics app

fields.title: commercetools
fields.description:
### About the commercetools app 

The commercetools app lets editors easily add a product and/or a product category directly from their commercetools account and reference it in Contentful entries.

Products and categories can be previewed via the Contentful web app, simplifying workflows for content editors. This enables them to use the latest products and categories across retail sites and experiences.


---

### Features:

- Directly link a product or a product category on commercetools to entries
- Browse products or product categories on commercetools in Contentful 
- Preview the selected product or product category in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need a [commercetools](https://commercetools.com/) account.


---

### Screenshots:

![apps-commercetools-cover](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/1HxHkx5n8CQ0q89xvWyl9Q/4a4e03dc6c8a14421d5009d410acf7e6/apps-commercetools-cover.png)
fields.tagLine: Connect products with content via the commercetools app

fields.title: Cloudinary
fields.description:
### About the Cloudinary app 

Link your Cloudinary asset library with Contentful to make the publishing process quick and seamless for your content editors. 

The Cloudinary widget allows editors to easily select digital media from their Cloudinary account without leaving the Contentful web app. 

---

### Features:

- Directly link your assets on Cloudinary in your Contentful entries
- Browse your asset collection on Cloudinary
- Preview selected assets in Contentful
- Standard JSON based asset reference format

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need:

- An account with Cloudinary
- Your Cloudinary account cloud name 

---

### Screenshots:

![Cloudinary dialog](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/4QAxpe5mbLZWkTAWucplJ4/1155818e1422f30fac24a51aab302670/apps-cloudinary-dialog.png)
fields.tagLine: Seamlessly deliver images and videos with the Cloudinary app

fields.title: Dropbox
fields.description:
### About the Dropbox app 

The Dropbox app lets users select any media or file from a personal or shared Dropbox account and attach it to an entry in Contentful.  

Simply click __Select__ or __Upload__ a file on Dropbox and select the assets you want to be referenced from your entry. 

---

### Features:

- Link your assets in Dropbox to your Contentful entries 
- Browse your Dropbox account
- Preview selected assets in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need a [Dropbox](https://www.dropbox.com) account.

---

### Screenshots:

![Dropbox screenshot](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/5uQPU1n35hheQmxg7CeMfx/95355daf5e17e7384e45ca37923722e3/Screen_Shot_2019-11-13_at_15.04.34.png?w=1000)
fields.tagLine: Connect Contentful and Dropbox to easily share content

fields.title: Bynder
fields.description:
### About the Bynder app 

The Bynder app allows editors to select media from their Bynder account without leaving Contentful. Design and marketing teams can easily access their most recent assets. 

Simply click __Select__ or __Upload__ a file on Bynder and select the assets you want to be referenced in your entry.

---

### Features:

- Link your assets on Bynder from your Contentful entries
- Browse your asset collection on Bynder
- Preview selected assets in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need:

- An account with Bynder
- The URL of your Bynder account
- A content type with a field of type JSON object to hold the references to Bynder

---

### Screenshots:

![apps-bynder-dialog](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/36TMeTeEpwqraMSTldDeVH/3ed9980af3eb5318d5631c3c6ef3e5f3/apps-bynder-dialog.png)
fields.tagLine: Find and use brand, marketing and product assets from your Bynder library

fields.title: Image Focal Point
fields.description:
### About the Image Focal Point app 

The Image Focal Point app allows you to set a focal point for an image, helping content editors center an image and crop it effectively for different devices and screen sizes. 

During the installation, the app sets up a content type you can use for your images with focal point data and provides you with a widget to set the focal point.

### Features:

- Visually set a focal point of an image to enable cropping for various types of devices
- Store coordinates of the focal point alongside image references

---

### Screenshots:

![apps-image-focal-point-dialog](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/2TuSk1vWvUU0SJ8O5Qsz9a/51ce3e4c6b1d8fab44171ebd22efbdfa/Optimized-apps-image-focal-point-cover.png)
fields.tagLine: Optimally crop images for different screen sizes with the Image Focal Point app

fields.title: Commerce Layer
fields.description:
### About the Commerce Layer app 

The Commerce Layer app lets you easily link products by their SKUs to entries in Contentful. 

Products that are linked from Commerce Layer can be easily previewed via the Contentful web app, making it easier for content editors to use the most recently uploaded products across catalogs and sites.

This app brings SKUs into your content so that you can make them viewable on your Contentful powered products.
 
---

### Features:

- Link one or more SKUs inside Contentful
- Full-text search for products in Contentful
- Preview selected products in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use the app, you will need a [Commerce Layer](https://commercelayer.io/) account.

---

### Screenshots:

![apps-commercelayer-cover](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/5lnMgJnXfyu8mroWsUuriw/6e2de078a754025c4c2f96c0a92c0e74/apps-commercelayer-cover.png)
fields.tagLine: Add enterprise-grade ecommerce products with the Commerce Layer app

fields.title: Shopify
fields.description:
### About the Shopify app 

The Shopify app connects your ecommerce platform, whether it's a store, online marketplace, social media platform or in-person point of sale, with your content in Contentful. 

The app allows editors to easily select products from their Shopify account and reference them inside of Contentful entries. Buyers have a consistent shopping experience no matter where they interact with your products.

---

### Features:

- Link your products on Shopify to your Contentful entries
- Browse your products on Shopify from Contentful  
- Preview selected products in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use this app you will need a [Shopify](https://www.shopify.com/) account.

---

### Screenshots:

![apps-shopify-cover](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/1XmpgI3BYDgjrceLD1Vc06/2fc5825ffdaaaeed4074a4743bdf86fa/apps-shopify-cover.png)
fields.tagLine: Integrate engaging ecommerce experiences with the Shopify app

fields.title: AI Image Tagging
fields.description:
### About the AI Image Tagging app

The AI Image Tagging app gives you the ability to automatically add searchable tags to images using AI.

This app is currently __offered for free on a fair use basis__. See the [documentation](https://www.contentful.com/developers/docs/extensibility/apps/ai-image-tagging/) for Fair Use Policy.

---

### Features:

- Automagically tags images using AI
- Manually tag images
- Store tags alongside image references
fields.tagLine: Automate tags on visuals with AI Image tagging app

fields.title: Frontify
fields.description:
### About the Frontify app:

Frontify is a brand management platform. With the Frontify app in Contentful, you can access your brand assets, ensuring all your content is brand compliant across all digital touchpoints. 

Simply click __Select__ files from Frontify to select the assets you want to reference from your entry.

---

### Features:

- Directly link your assets on Frontify from your Contentful entries
- Browse your assets on Frontify
- Preview selected assets in Contentful

---

### Requirements:

To use this app, you will need:

- An existing Frontify enterprise account
- The URL of your Frontify account

---

### Screenshots:

![contentful-frontify](//images.ctfassets.net/lpjm8d10rkpy/5onQHIH2JzKegzYZs2bWME/6f80663fdd4b801f5f3185798741e898/contentful-frontify.png?w=1000)
fields.tagLine: Connect with Frontify to access brand style guides, pattern libraries and design systems
